{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Already reviewed Step 6, 2 blocking items pending fixes",
    "content": "Thanks — I have already completed my initial review of Step 6 at commit 0143878 and sent detailed feedback to Luca. No new commits have landed since then.\n\nMy review found **2 BLOCKING items** that must be fixed before I can give consensus:\n\n1. **Focus management missing on project detail page** — `templates/project_detail.html` loads no focus management script. `project-focus.js` only covers the projects list page. When a user completes a next action on the detail page, the `<li>` is removed via HTMX outerHTML swap and focus falls to `<body>`. A `project-detail-focus.js` (or equivalent) is needed, scoped to `.project-action-item`, falling back to `#project-action-title`.\n\n2. **Stalled flag text color fails WCAG AA contrast** — `.project-item__stalled-flag` in `static/css/main.css` (line 1803) uses `color: var(--color-warning)` (oklch 0.75) on `background: var(--color-warning-light)` (oklch 0.93), giving approximately 1.5–2:1 contrast ratio. WCAG AA requires 4.5:1 for text. Fix: change to `color: var(--color-fg)`.\n\nI am standing by for re-review once Luca commits fixes for both."
  }
}
